reviews.text: Have been to Nara in Thai, i think this HK chain is good too, constantly I can hear the chef using wok and the airy flame sound from the stove, there are chefs cooking instantly in the kitchen. Unlike many restaurants serving heated pre-made food to save cost. Portion is generous, and tom yum soup can be a little spicier
Food was good. Loved the coconut smoothie. In front it looks nicer.

The food here feels like it over-engineers Thai food without really getting the basics right. Spice blends are not balancing really well, and a lot of food is trying to be an innovative fusion but forgot tasty, books flavours to begin with. The service is standard but the dining hall is nice and allows a certain ambiance.
Expensive for what your getting. The ambiance is nice, but the food really ain't that good
Food is good, esp the steamed fish with citrus and chili

Very good mall with lots of good brands. Have very good promotional offers for luxury skin care brands. Purchased Estee lauder skin care set at more than half off the price

result.name: New Town Plaza Phase 1

reviews.text:
The best shopping mall in Hong Kong:
1. itself + 6 more shopping malls, all inter-connected by enclosed air-conditioned walkways
2. Accessible by train, bus, minibuses, bicycles, private car (tons of parking space)
3. friendly affordable prices - not the Landmark or Pacific Place
It's easy to go around the place, convenient, but sometimes feel like the mall is kind of small.

It's the biggest mall in the region. Its been undergoing gentrification over the past few years. Local unique shops are being replaced by luxury chains. Car park is big but fills up quickly, and is expensive.
New Town Plaza Phase I is where you find the important shopping, City Super and lower level restaurant hall. There is direct access from the MTR Station and Shatin Park.
At Parkview : delicious food and good service👍

reviews.text: 商店按分類排列👍🏻
非常多內地客😥

成個商場嘅格局越嚟越似海港城，已經為自由行，而唔係再為沙田居民而設。
除非你真係好想買名牌，或者上食層食嘢，否則都係唔嚟好過！
小心俾自由行嘅巨型拖喼轆到隻腳， 成個商場比較行得舒服嘅係citysuper，起碼自由行唔會喺度買食材然後返屋企煮飯！

result.name: NARA THAI CUISINE

reviews.text:
CP低嘅高級泰國餐廳
**********************************

Nara係泰國好出名嘅餐廳，香港分店午市時段有lunch set，環境座位都幾舒服。✔️

✔️午市好多人，比較嘈雜。職員好有禮貌招呼入座，午市套餐係一整個餐盤上，賣相好靚。

🔆泰式和牛船麵 - 講真味道係幾好，但湯太少，河粉好快已經熟晒兼黐埋一舊。生熟牛肉同牛丸嘅味道都幾好，不過牛丸唔夠熱，只能夠用暖黎形容。

🔆泰式豬肉炒河粉 - 豬肉唔鞋口，河粉係大塊嘅泰式河粉，味道幾ok，不過又係衰在唔夠熱。
午餐送泰式肉碎沙律及湯 - 椰子雞湯過咸又太杰，唔推介。反而泰式沙律味道酸酸辣辣，惹味醒胃幾唔錯。

🤨百幾蚊一個lunch，如果想食環境嘅係唔錯嘅選擇。但如果你係想食同等CP值嘅食物，咁可能你要搵過第二間。。。
高級泰國菜，味道不錯，偏辣。應該可以要求少辣。放盤都不錯，服務員主動有禮。要俾個like

味道唔錯, 點左5款食物唯一覺得炸蝦餅比較遜色(可以唔試😂), 其他4款: 炒通菜, 醬汁好入味! 炒金邊粉 好大碟, 味道唔錯。菜肉包, 無諗過係肉粒😂😂 開頭食覺得幾好味, 不過食左一半之後覺得咸。最後既生蝦香港黎講, 價錢味道都不過不失😗 (2個人食左490蚊)
同埋個到啲侍應好好, 雖然我當晚星期五去, 屬繁忙時段, 但係佢地成日都會keep住倒水比我地, 而且都好有笑容🌹

Have been to Nara in Thai, i think this HK chain is good too, constantly I can hear the chef using wok and the airy flame sound from the stove, there are chefs cooking instantly in the kitchen. Unlike many restaurants serving heated pre-made food to save cost. Portion is generous, and tom yum soup can be a little spicier
環境不錯，多人排隊，最好先預約。服務態度OK，食物口味一般般
